The paper deals with combinatorial auctions, which are a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and involve algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of private valuations and budgets suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), while the focus on efficiency and optimality is relevant to the field of economics and computation (cs.EC). Finally, the mention of incentive compatibility and Pareto-optimality suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
